[<del>July</del> June 25, 1935]
Dearest Girls: 
Mama has told you that we reached here yesterday evening (or maybe she hasn't yet, but so it was.) On the way over we drove up from Harkins to where I taught school 37 and 36 years ago. We are in the cabin we occupied last fall & Mama is delighted with it. I don't know how long we'll stay here, but any mail sent here will reach us. I've written P-D stuff all morning & have more than enough already. 
It was bully in Wayne, & Mama & I are very happy over it all. I had an auditorium full for the Messiah Friday at 9:30. Then I talked at Chapel at 10:45, not knowing in the least what i was going to say, and I was astonished at the result. Then on Saturday, I wrote you, the Governor failed us & I was asked to take his place making the main Jubilee speech. 

